			"editorData": {
				"HowToTrigger": {
					"type": 23,
					"value": "This triggers in Wyrm's Crossing after an encounter with one of Orin's Impersonations.\r\n\r\n1) Gyldro Angleiron the Smith near the center of Rivington. (-7.119; 49.958; -58.56)\r\n\r\n2) Lens the Journalist near the entrance of the checkpoint. (6.372; 41.108; 23.997)\r\n\r\n3) Rowan the Flaming Fist near the back entrance of Big Barn near the refugee camp. (101.814; 44.018; -115.137)\r\n\r\n4) DyingAttacker (Dying Stone Lord Thug) near the entrance of the Smugglers Cave. (-142.784; 3.656; 72.951)\r\n\r\n5) Zethino the Love Dryad in the Circus. (-57.016; 45.094; -52.712)"
				},
				"defaultAttitudes": [
					{}
				],
				"defaultEmotions": [
					{}
				],
				"isImportantForStagings": [
					{}
				],
				"isPeanuts": [
					{}
				],
				"needLayout": {
					"type": 19,
					"value": 0
				},
				"nextNodeId": {
					"type": 5,
					"value": 5
				},
				"speakerSlotDescription": [
					{}
				],
				"synopsis": {
					"type": 23,
					"value": "Orin may impersonate several people in Wyrm's Crossing. The possible impersonations are :-\r\n- The Smith in Rivington\r\n- Lens the Journalist near Southcheck Point.\r\n- LoveDryad in the circus\r\n- Rowan the Flaming Fist at the big barn.\r\n- DyingAttacker at the Smuggler's Cave.\r\nInstead of these NPCs, Orin may take their place and impersonate them. \r\n\r\nThis PAD dialog is meant to be played after she reveals herselfs and teleports away. First one should recognise Orin by name (to help the player), and acknowledge her shapeshifting ability. Second can be more flexible, wondering why she's doing it."
				}
			}
		}
	}
